This subject was disscused a year+ ago, but no real solution to this
problem was implemented since then:

  http://www.hpc.uh.edu/fvwm/archive/9903/msg00230.html

In two words the problem is that if you have a module MyAlias2, all its
configuration will be passed to MyAlias module as well, which may result
in fatal errors for some modules.

If the syntax enables conflicts they will come (remember FormFvwmTalkHelp;
we at fvwm-themes have many such cases), Of course it is possible to solve
every individual conflict, but, instead, the conflicting syntax should be
resolved, i.e. introduced an alternative one.

I have a small patch, solving this problem. So both syntaxes are valid:

  *FvwmMyPagerLabel 0 Desk
  *FvwmMyPager:Label 0 Desk

Everything is fully backward compatible, but if you use the second (new)
variant, it is guaranteed that the configuration will only be passed
to FvwmMyPager and not, for example, to FvwmMyPage module.
The current implementation converts the new syntax to the old one (while
keeping the exact matching), because many modules rely on the old syntax,
but in the future, I hope, we could make a conflicting syntax obsolete.

Why I used colon? Originally Steve and Dan suggested colon, and I don't
care, as long as there is no conflict. Asterisk can't be used because of
DestroyModuleConfig, period can't be used because of the current FvwmForm.

The sooner a non conflicting syntax is introduced the better. We already
have in fvwm-themes about 50 module aliases for at least 6 FvwmModule's.
As a side note, we use a FvwmModule-SubName naming scheme for them,
which is just fine with a non conflicting syntax.

I want to apply this or similar patch before 2.4. Please comment.

Regards,
Mikhael.
