> I don't understand.  All modules should be able to use the period.

Using a delimiter in module names is not a good idea, this is a hack,
which makes file names ugly and does not disallow conflicts in general.
Say you have MyAlias2. with a period at the end, still MyAlias module will
get its configuration. You can't force a delimeter in module alias names,
the solution is to make a delimiter a part of the syntax (your idea).

I really don't care if FvwmForm aliases remain the same as now, we only
need to be able to use a non conflicting syntax, so, say, configuration of
FvwmEvent-Sound will never be passed to a FvwmEvent module with no alias.
And as I wrote, it is easily solvable.

Regards,
Mikhael.
