been
about a year and when I downloaded again this year - same problem.

When running the ./configure program it looks for the C compiler.  It
correctly finds the compiler to be CC.  But it then tries to do a test
compile and ./configure generates:

checking whether the C compiler (/usr/bin/CC -o32 -g -fullwarn -DIRIX -o32
-shared -demangle) works... no

which then generates:

configure: error: installation or configuration problem: C compiler cannot
create executables.

and aborts.

Has nothing been done to correct the problem in either FVWM or automake? 
Let me know!
