I'm answering my own question in hopes of having this info added to the FAQ. 
  This took me awhile to figure this out since its not mentioned anywhere 
even though it might be understood by the masses.

After an "xmodmap -e blah blah" or "xmodmap filename" one _must_ either 
restart fvwm to see the affects or add those commands to one's startx or 
xinitrc file and reboot.  Bare in mind that the changes show-up immediately 
when queried command-line in an xterm or xev or xkeycaps (kinda confusing to 
a newbie like myself).

Do please add this note to the FAQ, it might help another poor soul.

Now if I can only figure why my diamond key (SUN keyboard) does not function 
as a Meta key in fvwm (it does fine in emacs).  In Fvwm I have to use the 
Alt key --- Does fvwm map Mod1 as Meta by any chance ???

Thanks again.

Tim
